Notes.Note: Rather than having a cross-reference table for every other table, could have a single cross-ref with "TableNameCV" and "TableNameID" where the concatenation equals the primary key of the target table.

We could have a single cross-reference table. But, we would lose referential integrity with the tables that reference it as there would be no way for all of the table to share a single foreign key column.
In the barebones implementation: Actions are all ObservationActs on a SamplingFeature by at least one Person using a Method producing at least one ResultsSet.
Reasons for separating ObservationActs from ResultsSets: 1. Allows Results for many Variables from each ObservationAct 2. Allows for other ActionTypes
A person does not need to be associated with an Organization, but, an Affiliation record must be created for each person because that is how people get linked to actions.
Secondary contact info can be added as an Extension property
DataValues are not included in the Core to allow for Catalog implementations. Also, DataValues are stored in different tables according to the ResultsSetType
An ObservationAct is the only ActionType that can produce a ResultSet.
A ResultsSet describes metadata for one or more DataValues that are stored in Results tables specific to the ResultsSetType
In OGC O&M, these two tables are functionally concatenated into "Observations". i.e. each ObservationAct produces exactly 1 Result (which could include a coverage containing many values in a series).
Maybe Datasets should be linked to Actions rather than Results? Actions already group Results.

If EquipmentType is Instrument or Sensor (i.e. if it can produce Results), then a ConfigurationAction is required to specify output Variables that can be observed during an ObservationAct.
A ConfigurationAction can also be used to record metadata regarding the creation of a ParentEquipment from other Equipment.
CalibrationStandards can be considered a Specimen Type with specified source metadata and with known Values for one or more Variables

ConfigurationActions, CalibrationActions and MaintainenenceActions are all Types (or subclasses) of Actions that can be performed on equipment, sensors or instruments. Note that each of these Action Types is represented in a new table with a 1 to 1 or 1 to 0 relationship with Actions.

O&M ResultTime meaning: "the time when the result became available". It's useful to conceptualize Results as a catalog of values. So, having an XYZT bounding box may be useful, though that's available from Actions and SamplingFeatures.
OGC O&M documentation Page 25 in: Cox_10-004r3_Topic_20_Observations_and_Measurements.pdf Sampling Model: https://www.seegrid.csiro.au/wiki/AppSchemas/ObservationsAndSampling#Sampling_model
SamplingFeatureTypeCV: SamplingPoints, SamplingCurves, SamplingSurfaces, SamplingSolids
Sites is a special, widely used SamplingFeature type that's a Point (XY) Geometry. But named, polygon (XY) spatial units (watersheds, admin units) should also be accounted for.
Recommendation for ODM2 regarding Specimens: A specimen will not have location information. That information will be associated from its parent SamplingFeature, via FeatureParents
FeatureParents table enables parent-child relationships between any SamplingFeatures, including between Specimens and allowing composites (i.e. multiple parents).

OGC O&M considers Points, Curves, Surfaces and Volumes all as SpatialSamplingFeatures, in which "the value of a property varies within the scope of the feature." Therefore these SamplingFeatures can be used to record Coverage results.
See OGC O&M documentation for examples of different types of SamplingPoints, SamplingCurves & SamplingSurfaces and their respectively required attributes/metadata.
